docs.abstract: Hospitals and private investors keep pumping vast sums of money into an advanced type of radiology whose effectiveness, in many cases, has not yet been shown to justify its price.
docs.snippet: Hospitals and private investors keep pumping vast sums of money into an advanced type of radiology whose effectiveness, in many cases, has not yet been shown to justify its price.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On March 29, Georgetown University Hospital opened a proton-therapy cancer unit that is expected to treat about 300 patients a year at premium prices using what its proponents promote as the most advanced radiology for attacking certain tumors.

headline.main: For Cancer Centers, Proton Therapy’s Promise Is Undercut by Lagging Demand
headline.print_headline: An Advanced Therapy For Cancer Is Undercut By Lagging Demand

docs.abstract: The lawsuit claims the disgraced film producer blacklisted the actress after she rejected his sexual advances. Ms. Judd is suing for unfair business practices, defamation and sexual harassment.
docs.snippet: The lawsuit claims the disgraced film producer blacklisted the actress after she rejected his sexual advances. Ms. Judd is suing for unfair business practices, defamation and sexual harassment.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Ashley Judd sued Harvey Weinstein on Monday, opening a new legal battlefront for the disgraced film producer by claiming that her career withered because he spread lies about her in Hollywood after she rejected his sexual requests.

headline.main: Ashley Judd Sues Harvey Weinstein, Saying He Harmed Her Career
headline.print_headline: Judd Files Suit Claiming Weinstein Injured Career
